OL,3,COsian Roberts rules himself out of
OL,4,Crace to be new Wales manager
OL,6,F"I wish the Welsh national team every
OL,7,Fsuccess as it embarks on another
OL,8,Fexciting chapter, of which I have the
OL,9,Fmost wonderful memories.
OL,11,F"To the Red Wall and all the Welsh
OL,12,Ffans with whom I have gone through so
OL,13,Fmuch, the tears and the joy, I would
OL,14,Flike to thank you genuinely for the
OL,15,Fsupport I have always had from you and
OL,16,Fespecially in recent weeks. Diolch."
OL,18,FArsenal legend Thierry Henry and ex-
OL,19,FWales striker Craig Bellamy are among
OL,20,Fthe names reportedly being considered
OL,21,Fconsidered to replace Page.
